========
Overview
========

``pyramid_mongoengine`` is a simple Paster template or scaffold for the Pyramid Web
Framework. It provides URL mapping via traversal and persistence via MongoEngine.
It is based on the "starter" template included in Pyramid core, and Niall O'Higgins's
"mongodb" template.

See
  http://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/pyramid/1.0/narr/project.html#paster-templates-included-with-pyramid
  https://github.com/niallo/pyramid_mongodb.git

==========
Installing
==========

Latest stable releases can be found at http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyramid_mongoengine

You can install from Pypi using ``easy_install`` or ``pip``::

    easy_install pyramid_mongoengine

or alternatively::

    pip install pyramid_mongoengine


===
Use
===

Once ``pyramid_mongoengine`` is installed, you should see it in the list of
available templates when you run ::

    paster create --list-templates
    
if you use ``pyramid>=1.3`` ::

    pcreate --list-templates

::

  $ pcreate --list-templates
  Available templates:
    alchemy:        pyramid SQLAlchemy project using traversal
    mongoengine:    pyramid MongoDB project via MongoEngine
    starter:        pyramid starter project
    zodb:           pyramid ZODB starter project


You can create a project with MongoDB support by running ``pcreate -t pyramid_mongoengine``.


